The basic syntax for JS statements : 

1) let x  = 5 ;
2) let x = 5 
both are correct

let myVeryLongString = " this statement is too long for one line";

myFunctions(arg1, arg2, arg3, arg4);
OR
myFunction ( arg1,
arg2,
arg3,
arg4,
);
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
how to write comments : 
let x = 5; // this is a comment

// this is a 
// multi line comment

/* this is a better
multi line comment 
*/

-----------------------------------------------------------------
how to print things to the console : 

let someVariable = 100;
console.long(someVariable);

this prints "100" to the console
